Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 1056 \N"I Want My Husband Back"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[op]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[ed]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,[ed]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,[eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.77,0:00:03.98,9AM,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(625,1)}9AM \NMetropolitan Area Kasuba City
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.71,0:00:21.66,Mori,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(415,1)}Mori Fusae (76)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.08,0:00:21.66,DCMain,FUSAE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Is he dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.97,0:00:23.66,DCMain,FUSAE,0000,0000,0000,,He's not breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.84,0:00:27.76,Inukai,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(415,375}Inukai Hajime (35)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.00,0:00:26.31,DCMain,INUKAI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.81,0:00:28.79,DCMain,INUKAI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm sure he'll be fine once \Nhe's treated at a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.06,0:00:48.06,License,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Name: Butsumaru Daijiro DOB: February 20th \NAddress: Tokyo Beika City Haido 1056-9-10 \NIssued February 12th \NExpires March 20th Driver's License
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.61,0:00:45.90,DCMain,FUSAE,0000,0000,0000,,This must be his.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.90,0:00:48.06,DCMain,FUSAE,0000,0000,0000,,I should report this to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.91,0:00:56.65,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know the license \Nplate number or vehicle model?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.21,0:00:59.28,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,I've got bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.28,0:01:03.33,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,Butsumaru Daijiro hasn't \Nbeen taken to a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.63,0:01:05.58,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't been taken to a hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.85,0:01:08.58,DCMain,FUSAE,0000,0000,0000,,Then where did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.50,0:01:15.26,AccidentScene,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Scene of Accident
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.68,0:01:14.70,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Neither the company he manages nor \Nhis home have received any word.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.70,0:01:17.98,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The Kasuba police are searching \Nfor Butsumaru-san's whereabouts,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.26,0:01:17.26,Missing,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Missing Person \NButsumaru Daijiro-san (51)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.50,0:01:20.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A traffic accident victim just vanished, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.98,0:01:21.95,DCItalic,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}and are asking any witnesses \Nto contact the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.49,0:01:23.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When he was hit by the car...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.06,0:01:24.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He probably died.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.45,0:01:28.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit thought they could get away \Nwith it as long the body wasn't found,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.12,0:01:33.63,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so they pretended to take him to a \Nhospital and hid the body somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.44,0:01:37.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this is Detective Mori.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.26,0:01:38.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Who am I speaking to?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.25,0:01:42.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're the wife of the \Nmissing victim Butsumaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.63,0:01:46.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mysterious clouds block your field of view!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.43,0:01:48.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Clear them away with deductive \Nreasoning and the sky sparkles!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.28,0:01:50.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A missing victim, an unexpected demand,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.29,0:01:52.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and the truth that appears on \Nthe far side of negotiations!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.40,0:01:54.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.00,0:01:55.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.87,0:01:58.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.99,0:03:45.99,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(396,1)}I Want My Husband Back
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.68,0:03:43.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"I Want My Husband Back!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.99,0:03:47.49,Butsumaru,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Butsumaru
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.21,0:03:52.58,Emiko,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(415,375)}Butsumaru Emiko (46) \NDaijiro's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.37,0:03:52.06,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm Butsumaru Emiko, the \Nwoman who called earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.06,0:03:53.00,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}And this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.21,0:03:56.75,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm President Butsumaru's secretary Kadokura.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.22,0:03:56.54,Kadokura,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(415,375)}Kadokura Shinya (32) \NDaijiro's Secretary
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.06,0:04:03.51,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to find my husband \Nand bring him back safe and sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.82,0:04:06.76,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The police are looking for him,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.04,0:04:10.93,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,but I have no idea what he was \Ndoing in Kasuba in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.93,0:04:12.89,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't know anyone there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.08,0:04:17.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, I doubt your \Nhusband is still with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.73,0:04:19.96,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.49,0:04:26.16,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You want me to buy his body?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.15,0:04:37.17,DCItalic,SPEAKER,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I want you to buy the body \Nof your husband I hit with my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.80,0:04:39.25,DCItalic,SPEAKER,0000,0000,0000,,You need it, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.25,0:04:40.85,DCItalic,SPEAKER,0000,0000,0000,,You can't hold a funeral without it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.85,0:04:43.60,DCItalic,SPEAKER,0000,0000,0000,,I'll sell it to you for 10 \Nmillion yen, so get the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.60,0:04:45.99,DCItalic,SPEAKER,0000,0000,0000,,If you tell the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.99,0:04:49.93,DCItalic,SPEAKER,0000,0000,0000,,I'll dump the body in a faraway ocean \Nwhere it'll never be found again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.93,0:04:51.93,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,No! Please don't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.28,0:04:55.22,DCItalic,SPEAKER,0000,0000,0000,,I'll call your cell phone later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.15,0:05:03.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The two of them seemed somewhat \Nprepared to hear the news,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.73,0:05:07.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but what kind of monster kills a person \Nand demands money from their relatives?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.46,0:05:09.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We should report this to the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.47,0:05:10.27,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.27,0:05:14.62,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,If I can get my husband's body back for \N10 million yen, then I don't mind paying!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.24,0:05:21.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we don't tell the police, there's no \Nneed for you to comply with their demands.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.13,0:05:26.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The great Mori Kogoro shall take back \Nyour husband's body from the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.40,0:05:31.51,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,If that's possible, Mori-san, \Nthen of course I'd prefer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.67,0:05:35.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The question is how we'll find the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.67,0:05:40.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We might find some clues if we go to \Nthe scene of the accident in Kasuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.22,0:05:42.80,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,We'll join you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.16,0:05:58.86,DCItalic,INUKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried, but they don't \Nseem to have figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.54,0:06:01.79,DCMain,FUSAE,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I was so surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.10,0:06:05.06,DCMain,FUSAE,0000,0000,0000,,He came speeding down the street \Nwhile I was walking here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.62,0:06:08.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.61,0:06:12.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Stop resisting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.02,0:06:15.35,DCMain,FUSAE,0000,0000,0000,,That's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.90,0:06:17.53,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,He's the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.92,0:06:21.94,DCMain,INUKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I finally found a new job.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.37,0:06:25.44,DCMain,INUKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I was afraid of that going \Ndown the drain, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.79,0:06:28.86,DCMain,INUKAI,0000,0000,0000,,But I never demanded any money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.21,0:06:31.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know when to give up, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.28,0:06:33.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Quit stalling and return the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.21,0:06:35.93,DCMain,INUKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.65,0:06:42.93,DCMain,INUKAI,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.93,0:06:45.20,DCMain,INUKAI,0000,0000,0000,,This is where I buried it, but it's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.20,0:06:45.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.87,0:06:48.22,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.22,0:06:50.44,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,The president's body disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.64,0:06:53.57,DCMain,INUKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.91,0:06:56.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.39,0:06:59.64,Incoming,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Incoming Call \NIncoming call from withheld number \NWithheld Number Settings \NReject   Answer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.54,0:07:01.24,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.24,0:07:05.35,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,Your husband's body is crying \Nabout wanting to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.18,0:07:07.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This wasn't an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.57,0:07:09.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You just stole the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.00,0:07:11.66,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,Ding ding ding.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.81,0:07:15.05,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,It was quicker to say I killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.05,0:07:18.95,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,Only one old woman witnessed the accident, \Nso I figured I could pretend I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.51,0:07:21.35,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.85,0:07:26.47,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,I've decided to raise the price \Nof the body to 30 million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.47,0:07:27.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,30 million?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.94,0:07:31.68,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,30 million is fine, just \Ngive me back my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.68,0:07:33.26,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,That's the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.03,0:07:35.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,30 million is fine?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.54,0:07:40.39,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This person is weirdly obsessed \Nwith her husband's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.72,0:07:43.90,DCMain,INUKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Um, what's this about the body being stolen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.29,0:07:46.90,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They're probably an urban \Nexplorer or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.23,0:07:50.90,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and saw you hiding the body when \Nthey happened to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.90,0:07:53.41,Missing2,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Missing: Butsumaru Daijiro-san \NPlease contact the police with \Nany eyewitness information.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.17,0:07:53.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They got the idea when they saw the news,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.94,0:07:56.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,dug up the body and took it with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.87,0:07:59.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and demanded money in exchange for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.47,0:08:02.21,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Damn that body thief X.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.65,0:08:05.34,DCMain,INUKAI,0000,0000,0000,,But they didn't need to move the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.34,0:08:07.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What if you turned yourself in?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.88,0:08:10.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The police would've dug it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.27,0:08:12.72,DCMain,INUKAI,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why they needed to move it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.56,0:08:17.33,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, 30 million is an outrageous price.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.33,0:08:20.72,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's a small price to pay for \Nthe return of my husband's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.72,0:08:25.09,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, it'd be best if the great \Ndetective got it back for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.46,0:08:31.12,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand the ransomer either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.12,0:08:34.84,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why would they think she'd \Nbe willing to pay that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.82,0:08:49.13,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's Butsumaru-san's study.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.66,0:08:51.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.49,0:08:57.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.26,0:09:00.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't wander into rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.30,0:09:04.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister. What's this \Nthing stuck on the safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.75,0:09:08.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's an authentication device.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.82,0:09:09.27,NoMatch,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(210,1)}No Match
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.25,0:09:09.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.53,0:09:11.78,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.90,0:09:15.90,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Only my husband can open that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.26,0:09:21.91,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Inside that safe are our treasures, \Ntokens of our memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.69,0:09:25.76,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.76,0:09:28.42,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you can buy memories with money.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.04,0:09:35.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe there's actually money in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.73,0:09:39.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since she said she's willing \Nto pay 30 million yen,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.09,0:09:40.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,there could be several \Ntimes that in the safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.88,0:09:43.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, we have to find the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.65,0:09:45.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This has nothing to do with X.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.70,0:09:49.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about that? Doesn't \Nthis narrow down who X could be?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.44,0:09:52.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.56,0:09:56.13,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows about that safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.13,0:09:58.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I was wondering who knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.02,0:10:02.83,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Just the three of us. Me, \Nmy husband, and Kadokura.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.02,0:10:04.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.63,0:10:09.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There must be someone else, \Nand that person is X.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.78,0:10:11.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.71,0:10:16.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When you consider X demanded the \Nhigh price of 30 million yen
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.01,0:10:20.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and knows they need the \Nbody no matter what...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.64,0:10:23.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying someone who \Nknows about their situation
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.07,0:10:27.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,just happened to be there when \NButsumaru's body was being buried?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.18,0:10:28.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's too much of a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.89,0:10:31.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.96,0:10:35.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't X say something strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.60,0:10:40.16,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,Only one old woman witnessed the accident, \Nso I figured I could pretend I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.70,0:10:45.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Not even the news mentioned that an \Nold woman witnessed the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.11,0:10:51.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If they knew that, then maybe X was \Nthere when the accident happened, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.04,0:10:54.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What would X be doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.67,0:10:57.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We have to assume they were, or else—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.24,0:10:58.90,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, don't assume.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.90,0:11:02.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Someone who happened to get their hands \Non the body is just blackmailing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.22,0:11:07.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think this case is that \Nsimple. I think there's more to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.17,0:11:09.64,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I have guests over right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.64,0:11:12.60,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Did you notice anything strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.60,0:11:15.15,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,No, not particularly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.15,0:11:16.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.92,0:11:19.78,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-kun? What are you two doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.37,0:11:28.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.95,0:11:31.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what he's doing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.25,0:11:35.04,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He's the one who hid Butsumaru's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.65,0:11:37.55,DCMain,INUKAI,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Inukai Hajime.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.87,0:11:41.32,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You found the culprit and captured him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.32,0:11:46.81,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I guess there was no point in looking \Ninto Butsumaru's connections to Kasuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.14,0:11:54.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-kun, why didn't you let us know \Nright away when you captured the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.25,0:11:58.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd question him for clues first.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.11,0:11:59.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.34,0:12:00.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.04,0:12:02.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, Inspector,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.81,0:12:07.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,there's currently another ongoing case \Nstemming from the accident he caused.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.05,0:12:10.20,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,A second case?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.17,0:12:18.21,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I get the picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.36,0:12:24.22,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,What were the president's connections \Nto Kasuba you mentioned earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.54,0:12:29.00,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Butsumaru was renting an apartment in Kasuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.00,0:12:29.97,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,An apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.12,0:12:36.34,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The manager contacted us \Nafter seeing the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.34,0:12:39.79,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The name on the agreement is different, \Nbut they said he might be his resident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.79,0:12:44.61,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,When we took a look at the room he \Nstarted renting about a week ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.24,0:12:49.12,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,all we found was video equipment and alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.12,0:12:50.87,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Since he was renting it under a false name,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.87,0:12:53.62,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,we think it may have been a hideout \Nhe used to get away from things.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.77,0:12:56.51,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.16,0:13:01.83,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But why did he go to the apartment \Nin Kasuba that morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.62,0:13:05.01,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Was there some reason he had to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.01,0:13:10.39,DCItalic,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why he went, but it's \Nturned into this pain in the rear.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.85,0:13:19.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro-no-ojisan wanted me to ask you,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.72,0:13:24.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,yesterday morning, did you notice \Nanything strange about Butsumaru-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.68,0:13:28.86,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He seemed deep in thought, \Nwhich was unusual for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.32,0:13:31.60,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He received a call from Kadokura.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.14,0:13:35.45,DCItalic,BUTSUMARU,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I'll be all right, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.45,0:13:40.84,DCItalic,BUTSUMARU,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I took measures the other day \Nso I'll be fine even if they show up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.92,0:13:52.97,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He seemed to have something on his \Nmind and called Kadokura back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.35,0:13:56.10,DCItalic,BUTSUMARU,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to be late to work today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.28,0:13:59.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And then he headed to Kasuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.60,0:14:02.48,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What is Mori-san trying to figure out?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.48,0:14:04.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.42,0:14:09.24,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Has he figured out where this \Nmoney actually came from?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.00,0:14:11.37,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.13,0:14:16.30,Headline,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Suspected of Tax Evasion \NPresident and Chief Executive Officer Arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.83,0:14:16.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This must be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.74,0:14:18.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In which case...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.32,0:14:20.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.98,0:14:28.17,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Let's pretend we're complying with his \Ndemand and arrest X at the location of the deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.41,0:14:29.28,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.73,0:14:33.93,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's no room in this plan for \Nme to show off my detective skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.06,0:14:36.56,Incoming,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Incoming Call \NIncoming call from withheld number \NWithheld Number Settings \NReject   Answer
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.56,0:14:47.57,InCall,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,In Call \NEnd   Hold
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.95,0:14:38.27,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.27,0:14:41.07,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,Have you got the 30 million?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.07,0:14:43.47,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,Put it in a sturdy suitcase.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.47,0:14:46.07,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,We'll make the deal at Mt. Zangiyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.87,0:14:50.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why do they want it in a sturdy suitcase?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.04,0:14:53.69,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because it'll be \Neasier to run away with.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.69,0:14:55.71,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,I believe there's one in \Nthe president's study.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.33,0:15:01.33,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Mt. Zangiyama? I feel like \NI've heard that name before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.61,0:15:07.32,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my husband took Kadokura \Nthere once on an inspection.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.32,0:15:09.34,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted to develop the land \Nat the foot of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.58,0:15:11.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how you knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.81,0:15:13.85,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.17,0:15:15.77,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,What? Mori-san did?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.77,0:15:16.67,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.67,0:15:19.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently he got the \Ninspector's permission, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.37,0:15:21.04,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.63,0:15:28.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Chiba? I don't see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.54,0:15:32.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He left in a hurry. He said there \Nwas something he had to look into.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.98,0:15:36.44,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why'd he run off without my permission?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.44,0:15:38.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That calls for a pay cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.79,0:15:40.29,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.50,0:15:44.13,Zangiyama,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(375,375)}Metropolitan Area Mt. Zangiyama
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.63,0:15:49.30,InCall,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,In Call \NEnd   Hold
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.70,0:15:47.76,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,A whole bunch of you showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.76,0:15:49.30,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,See the shack to the west?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.72,0:15:53.90,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,One of you—you with \Nthe suitcase, you'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.30,0:15:55.79,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,Bring the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.29,0:15:58.56,DCItalic,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of you stay where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.86,0:16:01.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Are they watching us from in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.36,0:16:02.88,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's a cliff behind it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.41,0:16:04.81,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.81,0:16:06.82,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why they wanted the \Nmoney in that suitcase.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.08,0:16:17.11,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.11,0:16:19.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro-no-ojisan said not to tell anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.79,0:16:22.18,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,If Mori-san says so, then \NI'm sure it's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.66,0:16:26.08,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You, too, Takagi? Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.36,0:16:29.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have to cut his pay, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.39,0:16:33.84,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.86,0:16:43.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He still hasn't come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.95,0:16:45.65,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What's happening inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.36,0:16:53.36,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Kadokura-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.49,0:16:58.12,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He's all right. He's just unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.48,0:16:59.84,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.89,0:17:05.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad we got the body back, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.25,0:17:10.82,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,The moment I entered, I was \Nsuddenly struck from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.58,0:17:14.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Damn that X. They took the money \Nand escaped through there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.63,0:17:17.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, it'd be impossible to escape from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.00,0:17:20.56,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Then where did X go?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.42,0:17:25.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Where did...? Where did they...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.58,0:17:27.35,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.56,0:17:29.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit didn't disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.07,0:17:35.74,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What's that police officer \Ndoing with the suitcase?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.74,0:17:38.49,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And who's that woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.11,0:17:40.62,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So it was a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.18,0:17:46.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know who she is either, \Nbut she's most likely X.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.36,0:17:49.46,DCMain,MAYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What did I do, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.47,0:17:51.59,Hakase,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(415,375)}Hakase Mayumi (26)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.46,0:17:51.31,DCMain,MAYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}All I did was pick up \Nsomething someone dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.54,0:17:54.38,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}That dropped article is the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.76,0:17:57.13,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, the case has been resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.13,0:17:59.19,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Both the body and 30 million \Nyen have been returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.19,0:18:01.33,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,And the culprit was caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.33,0:18:03.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, we're only halfway done.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.62,0:18:11.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The mastermind who planned everything \Nand manipulated X still remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.02,0:18:14.28,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The mastermind?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.78,0:18:20.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, is this woman your \Ngirlfriend, Kadokura-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.61,0:18:22.48,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.96,0:18:27.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Kadokura-san is the mastermind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.17,0:18:29.17,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.27,0:18:36.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Butsumaru kept the money he made \Nevading taxes in that safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.70,0:18:40.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,However, perhaps because he felt uneasy \Nabout keeping the money at home,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.82,0:18:43.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,about one week earlier, he moved \Nit to another hiding place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.18,0:18:46.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Kadokura-san chuckled to \Nhimself when he learned that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.64,0:18:49.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You'd had your eye on that money that \Nwouldn't be reported to the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.30,0:18:50.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,even if it were stolen, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.32,0:18:53.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But you couldn't steal it \Nwhile it was in that safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.15,0:18:58.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,However, Butsumaru didn't tell you \Nwhere his new hiding place was.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.34,0:19:02.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So in order to find it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.33,0:19:07.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,you came up with the idea of directing Butsumaru\N there and having your girlfriend follow him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.70,0:19:10.21,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You put your plan into \Naction yesterday morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.71,0:19:10.71,Incoming2,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Incoming Call \NKadokura Shinya \NDecline   Answer
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.71,0:19:16.46,Headline,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Suspected of Tax Evasion \NPresident and Chief \NExecutive Officer Arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.01,0:19:16.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You told Butsumaru that someone had been \Narrested for tax evasion to make him anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.71,0:19:21.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He probably wanted to confirm he \Nwasn't being investigated secretly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.55,0:19:23.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Butsumaru played into your hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.41,0:19:25.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and your girlfriend followed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.42,0:19:29.93,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But on the way there, Butsumaru died \Nin an accident, and your plan failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.55,0:19:34.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,However, perhaps because you noticed something \Nsuspicious about the man who caused the accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.48,0:19:37.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,you came up with another way to get rich \Nquick after your first plan failed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.91,0:19:40.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,had her move the body...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.43,0:19:44.37,DCItalic,MAYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll sell it to you for 10 \Nmillion yen, so get the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.37,0:19:46.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,...and demand a ransom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.95,0:19:51.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The wife seems to think there's still \Na large amount of money in that safe,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.58,0:19:55.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so you knew she'd agree to pay a high price.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.67,0:19:57.50,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.77,0:20:00.89,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But it wasn't there anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.36,0:20:02.90,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Then where is the money?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.90,0:20:04.01,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I told you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.35,0:20:07.51,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Chiba, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.16,0:20:13.27,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,As Mori-san requested, after thoroughly \Nsearching the apartment in Kasuba,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.71,0:20:17.98,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I found roughly 350 million \Nyen in the closet ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.44,0:20:19.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.45,0:20:23.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He was renting that apartment in Kasuba \Nas a hiding place for the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.05,0:20:25.96,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he used a fake name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.87,0:20:29.12,DCMain,MAYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,350 million...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.12,0:20:30.41,DCMain,MAYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how much there was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.81,0:20:32.08,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk to me, you idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.08,0:20:33.94,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,Crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.94,0:20:35.73,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in pretending.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.73,0:20:39.09,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,At Mori-san's instructions, I was \Nwaiting at the bottom of this cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.94,0:20:53.45,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I saw with my own eyes the decisive \Nmoment proving you two are accomplices.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.45,0:20:55.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Inspector,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.38,0:20:57.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,the culprit X didn't vanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.47,0:20:59.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They were never here to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.96,0:21:04.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was all an act put on by Kadokura-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.12,0:21:08.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You probably learned about this shack
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.45,0:21:10.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,when you previously came here on an \Ninspection and figured you could use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.66,0:21:11.76,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,I never—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.76,0:21:14.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't try to make excuses, Kadokura-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.38,0:21:21.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The numerous calls you made to your \Ngirlfriend today are still in your phone's call history.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.03,0:21:26.43,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,I had to keep giving her instructions,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.92,0:21:30.93,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,like to raise the ransom to 30 million \Nbecause things were going well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.47,0:21:35.70,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the plan wouldn't work \Nwithout specific instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.28,0:21:40.19,DCMain,EMIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Why did he hide so much \Nmoney in an apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.77,0:21:43.94,DCMain,KADOKURA,0000,0000,0000,,It was supposed to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.27,0:21:47.70,DCMain,MAYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What an idiot. This was a huge loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.12,0:21:54.58,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They were all motivated by greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.20,0:23:18.20,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Detective Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.44,0:23:18.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Yes, that's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.40,0:23:19.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.62,0:23:23.21,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Someone was kidnapped and a ransom has been \Ndemanded in exchange for their safe return?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.48,0:23:29.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me more about this pet you were \Nkeeping secret from your landlord.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.22,0:23:30.97,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A pet, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.37,0:23:33.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A g-g-giraffe?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.81,0:23:38.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Just how large is their place?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.41,0:23:42.35,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is it even possible to \Nsecretly keep a giraffe?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.98,0:23:44.90,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Detective Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.98,0:24:09.01,DCEpPreview,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.61,0:23:52.14,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,It's an emergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.14,0:23:53.39,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,There's been an incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.04,0:23:56.93,DCMain,YOUNG WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.46,0:23:58.45,DCMain,OLD WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.74,0:23:59.83,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.08,0:24:02.59,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What's with those old ladies?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.59,0:24:06.25,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,We aren't thieves. We're the Detective Boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.01,0:24:15.01,DCNextEp,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Bad Guys
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.39,0:24:12.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "Bad Guys!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.03,0:24:34.95,Hint,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Sheets
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.54,0:24:33.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.05,0:24:34.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sheets!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:36.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Why do I keep getting jobs like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:39.95,Don'tMiss,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.65,0:24:37.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Probably because of how you act all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.81,0:24:39.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Zip it! Keep your bull-sheet to yourself!
